{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17480240","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17480240"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T23:39:49+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T23:39:49+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"29"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"29","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/29"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.81,0.05,0.02,0.06,0.06]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"29"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"92398"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"29","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/29"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"29"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"75711"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"3"},{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"107"},{"type":"tags","id":"4298"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4955"},{"type":"tags","id":"4966"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"6523"},{"type":"tags","id":"6610"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11629"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"31580"},{"type":"contributions","id":"31581"},{"type":"contributions","id":"34935"},{"type":"contributions","id":"41962"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44321"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"92398","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/92398"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 68-year-old woman presents with a four day history of pain and swelling in her right leg. Seven years previously she had a melanoma excised from the dorsum of her right foot and she had a deep venous thrombosis in the same leg 10 years earlier after a tibial fracture.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination her pulse is 90/min, blood pressure 116/70 mmHg and temperature 37.5\u00b0C. Her legs are shown in the illustration. (Image) The right leg is warmer than the left leg and is tender to touch.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely explanation for the changes?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Streptococcal infection","Haemosiderin deposition","Local spread of melanoma","Haemorrhage into the deep compartment","Arterial insufficiency"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe photograph shows that the right leg is uniformly swollen and reddened from immediately above the ankle to just above the knee. This is the classical appearance of cellulitis, which in this case is severe and circumferential. The usual organism responsible for this type of spreading \u003Cstrong\u003Einfection is Streptococcus\u003C/strong\u003E species. \u003Cem\u003EStreptococcus pyogenes\u003C/em\u003E (Group A streptococcus) and \u003Cem\u003EStaphylococcus\u003C/em\u003E \u003Cem\u003Eaureus \u003C/em\u003Eare the two most common pathogens overall, though atypical organisms may be implicated particularly when cellulitis arises in immunocompromised patients, injuries in aquatic environments, or bite wounds. Whilst such infections can occur anywhere, the leg is the most commonest site. In addition to the redness, some oedema is also visible. Whilst most cases of cellulitis are associated with infection from the individual\u0027s own skin flora, a history of local trauma (skin perforation) is not always present.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Streptococcus pyogenes (Group A streptococcus) and Staphylococcus aureus are the two most common causative pathogens in cellulitis."],"references":["Raff AB, Kroshinsky D. Cellulitis: A Review. JAMA. 2016 Jul 19;316(3):325-37. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27434444/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"75711"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"29"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"17470"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"17470","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/17470"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/5e3299a3-60a0-4e38-8af3-26b5381e84eb.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/5e3299a3-60a0-4e38-8af3-26b5381e84eb.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":587,"height":440}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"75711","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/75711"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-03-17T16:21:22+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-08-30T17:16:27+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"29"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"92398"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"3","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/3"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddf4","name":"Dermatology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:42+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"14","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/14"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udda0","name":"Infectious Diseases","synonyms":["ID"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2021-05-21T07:51:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","i